│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs when simplifyCFG tries to process a CleanupReturnInst and assumes its operand is a    │
│ CleanupPadInst, triggering a bad cast in getCleanupPad(). For IR with unreachable predecessors and certain      │
│ transforms, the cleanupret’s operand may not be a CleanupPadInst (e.g., could be a token/catchpad). The fix is  │
│ to guard against incompatible operand types before calling getCleanupPad() within SimplifyCFG’s                 │
│ removeEmptyCleanup/simplifyCleanupReturn path, and bail out if it’s not a CleanupPadInst so removeUnwindEdge    │
│ doesn’t assert. I will inspect the relevant files, implement a defensive check using dyn_cast, and run          │
│ submit-patch.                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                 │
